  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <head>To his louing Friend, <hi>D. Lupton.</hi>
   </head>
   <lg>
      <l>FEare not Momus, though hee Carpe,</l>
      <l>Nor Zoylus though hee snarle or Barke;</l>
      <l>Mirth is the Subiect of thy Booke,</l>
      <l>
         <pb facs="6"/>Citty and Country here may looke,</l>
      <l>Wonder at thee, and praise thy paine,</l>
      <l>That labour'd hast Sans hope of gaine?</l>
      <l>Thy Wit and Learning I Commend,</l>
      <l>To thee Applause, I freely lend:</l>
      <l>The wise will like, I wish the rest</l>
      <l>To spare their Censure, it is best:</l>
      <l>Theyle hurt themselues with their owne tong,</l>
      <l>Their Snarling can do thee no wrong.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>Per Samuel Perkings, <hi>Philomath.</hi>
      </signed>
   </closer>
</div>
